This is a Python library for accessing data via the WMATA Metro Transparent Data Sets API. More information is available at http://developer.wmata.com

------------------------------------------
Usage examples:

>>> from pywmata import Wmata

Initialize the API with your API key (available from http://developer.wmata.com/):
>>> api = Wmata(YOUR_API_KEY)

Get a list of all WMATA rail lines:
>>> lines = api.lines()
>>> print lines[0]
{u'DisplayName': u'Blue', u'StartStationCode': u'J03', u'EndStationCode': u'G05', u'LineCode': u'BL', u'InternalDestination2': u'', u'InternalDestination1': u''}

Get a list of all stations on the Green line:
>>> stations = api.stations('GR')
>>> print stations[:2]
[{u'Code': u'F11', u'Name': u'Branch Avenue', u'Lon': -76.911464217700001, u'LineCode4': None, u'LineCode2': None, u'LineCode3': None, u'LineCode1': u'GR', u'StationTogether2': u'', u'Lat': 38.826446348300003, u'StationTogether1': u''}, {u'Code': u'F10', u'Name': u'Suitland', u'Lon': -76.931870158899997, u'LineCode4': None, u'LineCode2': None, u'LineCode3': None, u'LineCode1': u'GR', u'StationTogether2': u'', u'Lat': 38.843964554400003, u'StationTogether1': u''}]

Get the rail path between stations D02 (Smithsonian) and D04 (Federal Center):
>>> rail_path = api.rail_path('D02', 'D04')
>>> print rail_path
[{u'StationCode': u'D02', u'SeqNum': 16, u'LineCode': u'BL', u'StationName': u'Smithsonian', u'DistanceToPrev': 0}, {u'StationCode': u'D03', u'SeqNum': 17, u'LineCode': u'BL', u'StationName': u"L'Enfant Plaza", u'DistanceToPrev': 2643}, {u'StationCode': u'D04', u'SeqNum': 18, u'LineCode': u'BL', u'StationName': u'Federal Center SW', u'DistanceToPrev': 1757}]

Get the current rail predictions for station F04 (Waterfront/SEU):
>>> predictions = api.rail_prediction('F04')
>>> print predictions
[{u'Group': u'1', u'Min': u'ARR', u'DestinationCode': u'E10', u'Car': u'6', u'Destination': u'Grnbelt', u'DestinationName': u'Greenbelt', u'LocationName': u'Waterfront', u'Line': u'GR', u'LocationCode': u'F04'}, {u'Group': u'1', u'Min': u'6', u'DestinationCode': u'E10', u'Car': u'6', u'Destination': u'Grnbelt', u'DestinationName': u'Greenbelt', u'LocationName': u'Waterfront', u'Line': u'GR', u'LocationCode': u'F04'}, {u'Group': u'2', u'Min': u'8', u'DestinationCode': u'F11', u'Car': u'6', u'Destination': u'Brnch Av', u'DestinationName': u'Branch Avenue', u'LocationName': u'Waterfront', u'Line': u'GR', u'LocationCode': u'F04'}, {u'Group': u'1', u'Min': u'11', u'DestinationCode': u'E10', u'Car': u'8', u'Destination': u'Grnbelt', u'DestinationName': u'Greenbelt', u'LocationName': u'Waterfront', u'Line': u'GR', u'LocationCode': u'F04'}, {u'Group': u'2', u'Min': u'14', u'DestinationCode': u'F11', u'Car': u'6', u'Destination': u'Brnch Av', u'DestinationName': u'Branch Avenue', u'LocationName': u'Waterfront', u'Line': u'GR', u'LocationCode': u'F04'}, {u'Group': u'2', u'Min': u'19', u'DestinationCode': u'F11', u'Car': u'6', u'Destination': u'Brnch Av', u'DestinationName': u'Branch Avenue', u'LocationName': u'Waterfront', u'Line': u'GR', u'LocationCode': u'F04'}]

Get a list of current rail incidents:
>>> incidents = api.rail_incidents()
>>> print incidents
{u'Incidents': []}

Get a list of current elevator incidents:
>>> elevator_incidents = api.elevator_incidents()
>>> print elevator_incidents
{u'ElevatorIncidents': []}
